Purpose

Lists the active maintainers of the EGTS project, their areas of maintenance, and their duties.

Definitions

· Maintainer: A contributor with merge rights and responsibility for day‑to‑day repository health.

Roles & Responsibilities

· GitDigital Products – Release management, security patches.
· RickCreator87 – Code review coordination, documentation upkeep.
· Maintainers must:
  · Triage issues within 72 hours.
  · Ensure CI passes before merging.
  · Update status files weekly.

Requirements

· Maintainers must be nominated by an owner and approved by GitDigital Products.
· Maintainers must complete a security and governance training annually.
· Inactive maintainers (no activity for 90 days) may be moved to emeritus status.

Current Maintainers

· GitDigital Products (primary)
· RickCreator87

Governance Alignment

Maintainer actions are subject to review by owners as defined in GOVERNANCE.md.

